a) A mapping G(x) = x - alpha*delf(x) 

   ||G(x)-G(y)||^2 = ||(x - alpha*delf(x)) - (y - alpha*delf(y))||^2

                   <= ||x-y||^2 - 2*alpha*[delf(x)-delf(y)]'*(x-y) + alpha^2*||delf(x)-delf(y)||^2
 
                   <= ||x-y||^2 - 2*alpha*[sigma*L||x-y||^2-||delf(x)-delf(y)||^2]/(sigma+L) + alpha^2*||delf(x)-delf(y)||^2
                   <= (1-2*alpha*sigma*L/(sigma+L))*||x-y||^2 + alpha*(alpha-2/(sigma_L))*||delf(x)-delf(y)||^2
 
                   <= (1-2*alpha*sigma*L/(sigma+L))*||x-y||^2 + alpha*max[L^2(alpha-2/(sigma+L), sigma^2(alpha-2/(sigma+L)]||x-y||^2
 
                   = max[(1-alpha*L)^2,(1-alpha*sigma)^2]||x-y||^2    
  
  An alternative solution contains eigenvalues max[(1-lambda*L)^2,(1-lambda*sigma)^2]

